  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Force Couple Equivalents"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "All forces, moments and couples acting on an object can be simplified into one force and one moment (or couple). This",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "force-couple pair is called a force-couple equivalent.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The singular force is equal to the resultant force of all the force vectors.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The single couple is equal to the combination of all moments from forces and couples about a chosen pivot point",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Calculating-the-Force-Couple-Equivalent",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Calculating the Force-Couple Equivalent",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The force couple equivalent is actually two values:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The resultant force vector",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "The resultant moment couple",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "orderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "However, the resultant force is represented as a vector, with magnitude ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$F$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " and direction ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "$\\theta$",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " (anticlockwise from the",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "positive X axis, in radians). Mathematically, this is represented as:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "R = sqrt{R_{x}^2 + R_{y}^2}",
            "\\theta = \\tan^{-1}(\\frac{R_{y}}{R_{x}})",
            "M_{a} = \\sum_{i=1}^{n} F_{i} \\cdot d_{i}"
          ],
          "syntax" : "math",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Where:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$R$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the resultant force vector",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$R_{x}$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the x component of the resultant force vector",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$R_{y}$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the y component of the resultant force vector",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$\\theta$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the angle of the resultant force vector",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$M_{a}$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the moment about point A",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$F_{i}$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the force vector of the i-th force",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "code" : "$d_{i}$",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " is the perpendicular distance from the pivot point to the line of action of the i-th force",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Some-things-Im-unsure-about",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Some things I’m unsure about",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A single force N acting d away from the center of mass ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "certainly",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " can’t exert both N newtons of acceleration and N*d newton-meters",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "of torque. I’ll replace this section once I figure this part out.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
